channel.title: What ports do I change?
channel.description:
ok all, it is portfowarding time for me! :d
I went onto gaming applications then single port forward, and there is loadz of different ports! could someone tell me the correct port to change. these are the default ones..
HTTP FTP FTP Telnet SMTP TFTP finger NTP POP3 NNTP SNMP CVS SMS SMS
they go down is this order.. ok then there are 2 options next to each option either: TCP or UDP. then last but no least there is an ip like this: 192.168.1.0 the zero at the end you can change to what you need? it can have 3 digits in it? so could someone tell me what port to change.
Many Thanks James.[br][size=1]Posted on: May 31, 2007, 11:19:20 AM[/size][hr]can you have any of those ports, or do you have to have a set one?[br][size=1]Posted on: May 31, 2007, 11:37:41 AM[/size][hr]www.portfoward.com doesn't explain it enough for me!
